                            <comment id="13567661" author="gtully" created="Thu, 31 Jan 2013 14:19:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it looks better now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;there are a bunch of pitfalls of request/reply with temps over a network.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;temps are not persistent and are tied to the connection that creates them so  failures can occur when a connection fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;some appropriate mods to the test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;backup=false in failover - otherwise there is a race between failover restore and broker teardown of the old connection.
	&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;we can loose a replayed temp dest, if it arrives before the remove is complete.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Broker.setCacheTempDestinations - this helps with reply that occur before the destination is removed during failover. the cache keeps the message (a form of temp persistence)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;tracking DestinationDoesNotExistException - a reply may fail if it occurs during failover recovery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;tracking dlq due to failed forwards that result from DestinationDoesNotExistException&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
